## Handoff Documents

- @VISION.md — what we're building and why
- @ARCHITECTURE.md — tech stack, modules, data model, data flow
- @CONSTITUTION.md — hard rules (anti-flattening, depth tags, testing discipline)
- @SCOPE.md — what we're NOT building

## Rules

- Test-first: write the test BEFORE the implementation. No exceptions.
- Commit on green: every commit leaves the full test suite passing.
- Constitution authority: CONSTITUTION.md rules are non-negotiable.
- Log every simplification at the moment it happens (Article 5).
- When unclear, ask the human. Don't guess.
- Derive tasks from user BEHAVIORS, not feature NAMES (Article 3).

## Getting Started

This project was initialized with [agentic-dev-starter](https://github.com/albertdobmeyer/agentic-dev-starter).

**If handoff docs are still skeletal:**
Read the handoff documents above. Help the human complete them through structured planning — push for experience fidelity scenarios, negative assertions, depth classifications, and filmable success criteria.

**If handoff docs are complete:**
Follow the Spec-Kit workflow: `constitution > specify > clarify > plan > tasks > implement`. The slash commands in `.claude/commands/` guide each step.
